Usage: setLayerPreference [-help] <layer_name> [-color <string>]
                          [-isSelectable {1 0}] [-isVisible {1 0}]
                          [-lineWidth <integer>] [-stipple <string>]
                          [-stippleData <string>]

-help                      # Prints out the command usage
<layer_name>               # the name of the layer or the object type
                           # (string, required)
-color <string>            # a color name or a numeric RGB value
                           # (string, optional)
-isSelectable {1 0}        # whether the object is selectable (enum, optional)
-isVisible {1 0}           # whether the object is visible (enum, optional)
-lineWidth <integer>       # number of pixels in the border of the specified
                           # object (int, optional)
-stipple <string>          # information about the stipple pattern of the
                           # object (string, optional)
-stippleData <string>      # the stipple information for the object
                           # (string, optional)